TY  - JOUR
T1  - Strategic Planning and Firm Performance: A Synthesis of More Than Two Decades of Research
AU  - Miller, C. Chet
AU  - Cardinal, Laura B.
Y1  - 1994/12/01
PY  - 1994
DA  - 1994/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256804
DO  - 10.5465/256804
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1649
EP  - 1665
VL  - 37
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Building on previous contingency frameworks, we developed an encompassing contingency model that might explain the inconsistent planning-performance findings reported in previous research. The model was empirically tested using meta-analytic data drawn from 26 previously published studies. Results suggest that strategic planning positively influences firm performance and that methods factors are primarily responsible for the inconsistencies reported in the literature. The substantive contingency factors that we examined, some of which have been frequently cited as important by previous researchers, did not have a large impact.
AB  - Building on previous contingency frameworks, we developed an encompassing contingency model that might explain the inconsistent planning-performance findings reported in previous research. The model was empirically tested using meta-analytic data drawn from 26 previously published studies. Results suggest that strategic planning positively influences firm performance and that methods factors are primarily responsible for the inconsistencies reported in the literature. The substantive contingency factors that we examined, some of which have been frequently cited as important by previous researchers, did not have a large impact.
