TY  - JOUR
T1  - Effect of Announcements of Withdrawal from South Africa on Stockholder Wealth
AU  - Meznar, Martin B.
AU  - Nigh, Douglas
AU  - Kwok, Chuck C. Y.
Y1  - 1994/12/01
PY  - 1994
DA  - 1994/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256803
DO  - 10.5465/256803
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1633
EP  - 1648
VL  - 37
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this study, we analyzed investor reaction to corporate announcements of withdrawal from South Africa to determine whether such announcements increased or reduced firms' market value. We also examined the effect of the timing of the announcements on stock valuation. The announcements were associated with a significant drop in the value of the withdrawing firms' stock, particularly for firms withdrawing earlier in the debate surrounding the issue of withdrawal. These results suggest that managers were considering the interests of groups other than stockholders in their decisions to withdraw. Implications of the results for stakeholder theory are discussed.
AB  - In this study, we analyzed investor reaction to corporate announcements of withdrawal from South Africa to determine whether such announcements increased or reduced firms' market value. We also examined the effect of the timing of the announcements on stock valuation. The announcements were associated with a significant drop in the value of the withdrawing firms' stock, particularly for firms withdrawing earlier in the debate surrounding the issue of withdrawal. These results suggest that managers were considering the interests of groups other than stockholders in their decisions to withdraw. Implications of the results for stakeholder theory are discussed.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256803
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256803
Y2  - 2026/04/24
