TY  - JOUR
T1  - Bargaining Power, Management Control, and Performance in United States–China Joint Ventures: A Comparative Case Study
AU  - Yan, Aimin
AU  - Gray, Barbara
Y1  - 1994/12/01
PY  - 1994
DA  - 1994/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256796
DO  - 10.5465/256796
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1478
EP  - 1517
VL  - 37
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article reports a comparative case study of four joint ventures between partners from the United States and the People's Republic of China. The bargaining power of potential partners affects the structure of management control in a joint venture, which affects venture performance. Several informal control mechanisms interacting with formal control structure and influencing performance are identified. We also investigated the joint ventures' evolution over time. An integrative model of management control in joint ventures is presented.
AB  - This article reports a comparative case study of four joint ventures between partners from the United States and the People's Republic of China. The bargaining power of potential partners affects the structure of management control in a joint venture, which affects venture performance. Several informal control mechanisms interacting with formal control structure and influencing performance are identified. We also investigated the joint ventures' evolution over time. An integrative model of management control in joint ventures is presented.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256796
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256796
